Season: 1996-1997

Mali 1996/97


Championnat National de 1ère Division

Second Stage (Carré d'As)

Round 3 [May 8]
Stade Malien 1-6 Djoliba AC

Djoliba AC wins the championship.

Relegated: Commune II, AS Réal

Promoted: Débo Club (Mopti), Sonni (Goa)


Coupe National

Qualification Round

Ligue de Bamako
AS Réal         4-0 AS Commune VI
Stade Malien    1-1 COB Olympique       [1-1, aet; 5-4 pen]
USFAS and CSK also qualified

National Round
1/4 final [Jun 8]
CSK       6-0 AS Comatex        [on previous rounds, CSK wins against AS Mandé and Mamahira]
USFAS         0-0 Nianan            [0-0, aet; USFAS won on pen]
Stade Malien and AS Réal also qualified

Final
Stade Malien    2-1 AS Réal 


Coupe "Manpo" (1997)

Final [Mar 16]
Djoliba AC bt  AS Réal


Coupe BMCD (1997)

Semifinals
Djoliba AC      3-1 USFAS       [Oct 11]
CSK             bt  Stade Malien[Oct 12]

Final
Djoliba AC      bt  CSK


Coupe INPS (1997)

Final
Djoliba         3-2 AS Mandé

NB: first ever final Mandé


Coupe INPS (1997/98?)

1/4 final
Stade Malien    2-1 CSK         [Oct 18]

1/2 final 
Stade Malien    4-1 USFAS


Coupe "Promotion de l'Arbitrage" (1997)

1/4 final [Oct 25]
Stade Malien   1-0 Nianan
AS Réal            3-1 USFAS


